| Class and Object |
====================
👉 A Class is a blueprint or template used to create objects. 
   It defines the attributes (data) and methods (behavior) that objects will have.
    
    class Student:
        pass

======================
| What is an Object? |
======================
👉 An Object is an instance of a class. It is a real entity created from a class that contains actual 
   data and can perform actions.

    class Student:
        pass
    
    s1 = Student()

Student() -> Object
s1 -> Storing Variable

=======================================
| Difference Between Class and Object |
=======================================
_______________________________________________________________________
| Class                             | Object                          |
| --------------------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| Blueprint                         | Real Instance                   |
| Logical Entity                    | Physical/Runtime Entity         |
| Template                          | Actual Data                     |
| One class can create many objects | Every object belongs to a class |
_______________________________________________________________________


