| Constructor (__init__()) | -> Constructor Runs Automatically
============================
👉 A constructor is a special method that is automatically called when an object of a class is created. 
   It is mainly used to initialize the object's data (attributes).

     class ClassName:
         def __init__(self):
          # Initialization

    class Student:
    
        def __init__(self):
            print("Constructor Called")
    
    s1 = Student()

O/P : Constructor Called

-------------------------

